<br>
Other death was in guk, got attacked just as a friendly cleric cast invis vs undead on me.  Lucky for me he rezed me and invised me, nice guy I gave him some pp for his help.<br>
<br>
Every other one was easy, the 2 underwater goblin towers I got wolf form from a druid friend.  <br>
<br>
Good quest.  I am know +10 smarter <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaybranch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>faybranch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/26/01 8:19:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Got my Staff of Wheel!</span><hr size=1> Did you have any trouble with faction with Sulgar?<br>
<br>
I can't get him to give me the wheel case and I know it must be a matter of faction, as my friend was able to get it from him using the same phrases I was.<br>
<br>
I heard this guy used to be Beta Nuetral faction, but then I also heard that Beta Neutral faction had been removed from the game.  I think that the latter is true, because I tried some Beta Neutral quests and got no faction messages.<br>
<br>
Any idea how I can get Sulgar to like me?<br>
<br>
I petitioned a GM and all he told me was that the quest was not broken.<br>
<br>
Thanks. =) <p>Now-Springtide the wood elf warrior-Bertox<br> Obida the human shadowknight-Rodcet Nife</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/01 11:42:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Got my Staff of Wheel!</span><hr size=1> Noone I have ever head of was actually bad faction for Sulgar, they were just not getting the phraseing right on the responces. Just remember that the text is Tarton Wheel and NOT Tartons Wheel OR Tarton's Wheel. Once you get past that, try combinations of the words in brackets. Remember that if there are multiple paths of conversation in brackets, you cannot combine them in one reply. It will pick up the forst one it finds. So if the text looks like:<br>
mob_001 says, &quot;Yes, yes, I know [Carol] and [Greg] Brady have a bunch of [Kids], but which do YOU like?&quot;<br>
<br>
Carol, Greg and Kids are all separate topics, so the following statement will never get you to Greg:<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;What about Carol and Greg Brady?&quot;<br>
<br>
If you really did blow beta-neutral faction, there is a way in High Pass to earn some back with bloodstones. Fortunately you can both buy them there and turn them in. I forget the name of the mob you hive them to, however, but I think he's an erudite... <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Achieved Slayer<BR>
Assigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaybranch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>faybranch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/10/01 3:43:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Help!  If you can. </span><hr size=1> Thank you for the advice, but I am still stuck. =(<br>
<br>
I have gotten all of the rods, but Sulgar still won't give me the wheel case.  <br>
<br>
I know that I am saying the right keywords, because I recruited about five other players to come to Sulgar.  I told them word for word what to say, and they all got the case.  Here's what we used:<br>
<br>
what tarton wheel<br>
<br>
I am interested<br>
<br>
give me the wheel case<br>
<br>
So, I figured it was my Beta Neutral faction.  I went to High Pass Hold and did the bloodstone quest to get those gloves from the Erudite.  I did it many many times, but I noticed, that while it would give me experience, I was not getting any Beta Nuetral faction messages, or any other faction boosts for that matter.<br>
<br>
Thinking that maybe they'd changed his faction, I got mine up with the Order of Three in Qenyos ( its' the closest wizard guild to Sulgar ) but still no luck.  Oh, well.  Gotta try something.<br>
<br>
Finally, some people telling me that I had to petition a GM to reset my Beta Nuetral faction.  I petitioned, and was instructed to Email customer support.  Customer support told me that the quest was not broken, and that Beta Neutral faction was still in the game.<br>
<br>
So, that's where I stand.  10 rods, but no wheel case. hehe<br>
<br>
Anyway, if anyone knows any way for me to boost my Beta Nuetral faction and get in good with Sulgar, could you please let me know?  I have tried the bloodstone one, but it did not work.  There are two other ones listed on the Allakazam website, but I am not high enough level to do those yet.<br>
<br>
Any advice would be HUGELY appreciated.  <br>
<br>
The next thing I am going to try is to improve my faction with the Barbarians.  The guards still regard me dubiously, although I have my doubts that this is connected to Sulgar, as he regards me indifferently.<br>
<br>
Thank you,<br>
<br>
Azlin, <br>
Level 23 wizard cause I died so much in Lower Guk getting the last rod, hehe<br>
Bertox<br>
<br>
Man, I wish I knew what I did that screwed up my faction with Sulgar.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/10/01 8:06:29 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help!  If you can. </span><hr size=1> Sorry I can't be of more help. For grins, I tried the bloodstone quets in HPK beore I did the rod nd I definately got BetaNeutral faction. But I dont remember seeing it anywhere else in the game other than the SoTW quest. If they have gotten the boxes and you havn't, that much be the problem. But I am indiff to Sulgar, so I would think that it shold work...<br>
<br>
For Grins, These are what you are sayimg to him:<br>
<br>
what tarton wheel<br>
<br>
I am interested<br>
<br>
give me the wheel case<br>
<br>
You are punctuating all that AND have sulgar Targeted the whole time, right?<br>
<br>
If you dont punctuate correctly, they quest may not work.<br>
<br>
May I have the wheel case?<br>
<br>
is not the same as <br>
<br>
May I have the wheel case<br>
or <br>
May I have the wheel case.<br>
<br>
 <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Advanced Slayer, WurnSlayer<BR>
Assigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzupe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zupe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/10/01 10:36:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help!  If you can. </span><hr size=1> There have been reports of Sulgar not talking to ppl. Your beta-neutral faction may be off and you will need a GM to help you with that. If your faction was bad with him you should probably get an insult instead of silence. Talk to your local &quot;friendly&quot; GM and they might be able to assist. Only other thing I can think of is get right in his face. I know on some of the quests I have done that being just in melee range does not work, you have to be on top of them almost.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hope that helps <p><B>
