<b>Boobini Bobsalot</b> <BR>20 Uber Monky<BR>
<b>Aatien Soulseeker</b> <BR>34 Necromancer<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaybranch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>faybranch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/11/01 4:24:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Got my Staff of Wheel!</span><hr size=1> WOO HOO!<br>
<br>
Ennya, you are a genius!!!! <br>
<br>
( Either that or I'm just a total bonehead idiot, hehe )<br>
<br>
I tried Sulgar again, this time making sure that I had him targeted. I also stood so close to him that I was right on top of him, and BAM!  I got the wheel case!<br>
<br>
Your reply made me realize that sometimes I have a habit of un-targetting an NPC after I hail them, so I don't accidentally auto-attack them or something.<br>
<br>
Thank you so, much.  I know it may seem like a little thing, but it sure had me stuck!<br>
<br>
But now I have my Staff of the Wheel, thanks to you, Ennya.  <br>
<br>
Thank you, thank you, thank you!<br>
<br>
Azlin of Bertox<br>
Level 24 Wizard<br>
<br>
